    public interface ImmutableDataManipulator<I extends ImmutableDataManipulator<I,M>,M extends DataManipulator<M,I>>
extends DataSerializable, ValueContainer<I>
    An ImmutableDataManipulator is an immutable ValueContainer such that once it is created, any BaseValues exist as ImmutableValues. Any modification methods result in new instances of the same typed ImmutableDataManipulator.

    As with DataManipulator, it is always possible to translate back and forth between mutable and immutable with asMutable() and DataManipulator.asImmutable().
